BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20100123T170000Z
DTEND:20100123T193000Z
DTSTAMP:20260315T222701Z
UID:5todcd3pv5phqr8dm61sfss71c@google.com
CREATED:20100120T133256Z
DESCRIPTION:Mitch Altman\, most well-known for inventing TV-B-Gone\, a keyc
 hain that turns off TVs in public places\, but also a co-founder of Noisebr
 idge will be giving a workshop at the Node. He has a bunch of different pro
 jects\, including TV-B-Gone\, Brain Machine\, LEDcube\, Trippy RGB Waves\, 
 Mignonette Game\, and others for people to purchase and build. More info is
  on the “maker faire” tab on his website. Everyone can choose the project t
 hat most intrigues them. The cost of his parts are between $10 and $30\, de
 pending on the project. Bring your own soldering iron\, wire cutters\, help
 ing hands\, and solder if you have them. If you do not have these things\, 
 we will try to provide them. We have numerous wire cutters and some solder\
 , but the status of our soldering irons is a little sketchy. And one of our
  helping hands is maimed and is now only a single helping hand. 
LAST-MODIFIED:20230110T144924Z
LOCATION:120 W North Ave. Baltimore\, MD 21218
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:An Afternoon with Mitch Altman
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
