BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20100929T230000Z
DTEND:20100930T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260315T222701Z
UID:73bklogirclp196lluqkk6hvhk@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20100929T190000
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20100727T003244Z
DESCRIPTION:Rapid digital prototyping and fabrication technologies such as 
 3D\nprinting and milling have existed for decades\, but have been so\nexpen
 sive that they have remained largely in the hands of big\nmanufacturers or 
 researchers.  Now\, thanks to open source hardware\ninitiatives like RepRap
 \, 3D printing has become a hobby that you can do\nat home.\n\nMarty will t
 alk a bit about the current state of commercial\, community\,\nand desktop 
 3D printing\, and how one kit company in NYC\,\nMakerBot Industries\, is tr
 ying to turn this hobby into a revolution.\nHe'll also give a live 3D print
 ing demonstration on his printer\, MakerBot #131.\n\nMarty McGuire lives in
  Baltimore and is a web developer for MakerBot Industries.\nHe rides the Bo
 lt Bus quite often.
LAST-MODIFIED:20230110T145017Z
LOCATION:The Node
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Dorkbot - 3D Prototyping with Makerbot #131
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
