BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20100127T003000Z
DTEND:20100127T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20260315T222701Z
UID:kr2uahrmav38kpmjll8pv50qhg@google.com
CREATED:20100108T134746Z
DESCRIPTION:I’ve heard it in the Node before “I don’t know how to program” 
 and when I ask why it’s almost for a lack of belief that they can do it.\nW
 ell programming isn’t hard and I’m going to prove it\, on the 26th I’d like
  to take some time to introduce programming to non-programmers and see if I
  can get people started in the right direction.\nI am not an expert so the 
 subject matter we will explore will be extremely basic (variables\, iterati
 on\, flow control\, object orientation\, etc) and we will use Processing to
  do so. On the bright side\, once started with Processing you can begin to 
 get into more complicated concepts and decide where to go from there.\n** E
 mail matthew.forr@gmail.com if you plan to attend **\nFortunately for me Da
 niel Shiffman has done all the work and has a Processing workshop available
  on his website. If you are interested in this please bring a laptop with P
 rocessing installed and these files from Shiffmans website: \n\nhttp://www.
 shiffman.net/p5workshop/partI.zip \nhttp://www.shiffman.net/p5workshop/part
 II.zip\nhttp://www.shiffman.net/p5workshop/partIII.zip\n\nDownload processi
 ng here:\nhttp://www.processing.org/download/index.html
LAST-MODIFIED:20230110T144933Z
LOCATION:120 W North Ave.\, Baltimore\, MD
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Intro to Programming for Non-Programmers by a Non-Programmer
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
