UID:dbccf1lrjvoj0580nf9vv630q4@google.com
CREATED:20100108T134122Z
DESCRIPTION:Come check out the Techno-Swap-Fest!! The Node is a club sponso
 r of the event\, so be sure to stop by our table.\n\nWebsite: http://groups
 .google.com/group/techno-swap-fest\n\nAttention All Hobbyists\n\n    * Is y
 our workshop so cluttered that you can barely work on your projects?\n    *
  Did you buy something online that didn't fit into your plans?\n    * Are y
 ou still looking for that perfect gadget\, part or tool?\n\nIf you answered
  YES or NO to any of these questions\, you need to attend the 1st Annual Te
 cho-Swap-Fest to buy\, sell and gawk at all of the precious junk that other
  hobbyists crave.\n\nHere are just some of the hobbies expected to be repre
 sented:\n\n    * R/C (boats\, planes\, tanks\, cars\, trains\, geese\, mons
 ters)\n    * Robotics (competition\, combat\, R2D2\, micro-bots\, junk-bots
 )\n    * Electronics (hackers\, makers\, crackers\, phreaks\, HAMs)\n    * 
 Mechanical (steam engines\, CNC\, animatronics\, whimsical)\n\nAnd some of 
 the precious stuff (a.k.a. junk) you'll find:\n\nMotors\, gears\, tools par
 ts\, radios\, batteries\, materials\, wheels\, circuits\, gadgets\, cases\,
  plans\, complete projects\, never-completed projects\, models\, books and 
 much\, much more.\n\nDoor Prizes:  Most Unusual\, Least Useful\, Best Dust 
 Collector\n\nAll proceeds support the National Electronics Museum:\n\nEntra
 nce Fee:               Adults $5\, Kids under 16 FREE\nSeller's Table:     
          $10  (limited number\, reserve early)\nClub Sponsorship:        FR
 EE (just send us your info)
LAST-MODIFIED:20230110T145028Z
LOCATION:National Electronics Museum\, Linthicum MD
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Techno Swap Fest
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
