CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20101210T211847Z
DESCRIPTION:In honor of 60 years of Hamming Codes\, we're reading the origi
 nal paper (14 pages) by the man himself who believed that "the purpose of c
 omputing is insight\, not numbers."\n\nIt's a paper\, not a book\, and ther
 e's a fair bit of math in it\, but nary a Greek letter or an integral.  Mos
 tly arithmetic and thinking.  Hamming's work (with Claude Shannon\, perhaps
  the seminal mind of information theory) led directly to a lot about comput
 ers we now take for granted: compression\, error detection\, encryption\, a
 nd fast reliable networks.\n\nWe'll discuss\, drink wine\, eat cheese\, hel
 p each other out with the math (probably before the wine)\, and then pick a
  book for next time (so bring an idea and a pitch for it.)\n\nLinks:\nThe p
 aper: http://bstj.bell-labs.com/BSTJ/images/Vol29/bstj29-2-147.pdf\nMore on
  Hamming Codes: http://www.cio.com.au/article/369282/cio_blast_from_past_60
 _years_hamming_codes/\nMore on Hamming: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richar
 d_Hamming
LAST-MODIFIED:20230110T144557Z
LOCATION:Baltimore Node\; 120 W. North Ave\, Baltimore\, MD 21201
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Node Book Club - Hamming Codes
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
