BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20141025T170000Z
DTEND:20141025T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260315T222701Z
UID:pk699qfjrq8lv00l9hofo6gv7s@google.com
CREATED:20141014T150252Z
DESCRIPTION:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/blinkytile-beta-testing-workshop-t
 ickets-13674313239\n\nBlinkyTile is a system of LED lights on pentagonal ti
 les for creating dynamic light sculptures in (almost) any shape you can ima
 gine. Currently on its way to finishing a successful Kickstarter campaign\,
  we’re looking for beta-testers to give us feedback on the assembly and pro
 gramming of the BlinkyTile to help refine the final version that backers wi
 ll receive.\nBlinkyTile Beta Workshop\n\nIn this 3 hour workshop\, particip
 ants will prepare and assemble a 14-tile kit to make a dodecahedron lamp li
 ke the one seen above. Or\, make a shape of your own choosing!\n\nAfter sol
 dering the boards into a sculpture\, we’ll solder on the controller board a
 nd test everything out. Next\, we’ll cover how to program your BlinkyTile s
 culpture using the Arduino programming environment.\n\nTime permitting\, we
  may be able to cover more advanced topics such as controlling your BlinkyT
 ile sculpture via your computer using Processing.\n\nNo prior soldering exp
 erience is needed!\n\nFor each purchased workshop seat\, we will provide:\n
 * 14-tile kits\n* BlinkyTile controller board\n* 6-foot USB micro cable\n* 
 Solder and the use of a soldering station for assembly\n* Stranded wire for
  attaching the controller board to the finished sculpture\n\nParticipants m
 ust bring:\n* A laptop with the most recent Arduino (http://arduino.cc/) pr
 ogramming environment installed\n* [Optional] A dedicated power supply (e.g
 . 5V phone wall adapter or a 5V USB battery pack)\n\nDon’t forget\, October
  25th is the night of the Patterson Park Lantern Parade (http://www.creativ
 ealliance.org/events/2014/2014-great-halloween-lantern-parade-festival-kale
 idoscope).\nWe think your BlinkyTile sculptures would make an amazing addit
 ion!\n\nAbout this Workshop\n\nHosting for this workshop is graciously prov
 ided by the Baltimore Node Hackerspace. (http://baltimorenode.org/)\n\nWork
 shop fees are used to cover the costs of the hardware kits. All further pro
 ceeds go to fund the Baltimore Node.\n\nYour instructors for this workshop 
 are Baltimore Node members Marty McGuire and Amy Hurst.\n\nMarty McGuire is
  a freelance web developer in Baltimore\, MD. In 2013 he created applicatio
 ns and content for the successful Kickstarter campaign for the BlinkyTape.\
 n\nAmy Hurst is faculty at UMBC. Her research focuses on DIY and accessibil
 ity.
LAST-MODIFIED:20141014T150252Z
LOCATION:Baltimore Node Hackerspace\, 403 E Oliver St\, Baltimore\, MD 2120
 2\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:BlinkyTile Beta Workshop
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
