UID:mfksmmmvr4qfpco3i5alpb2b6g@google.com
CREATED:20100217T151448Z
DESCRIPTION:!!TICKETS!!\nhttp://www.eventbrite.com/event/567889573\n\nThis 
 is an intro to soldering workshop to kick off our series of monthly Arduino
  workshops. We will be learning to solder while assembling an Arduino Proto
 Shield to use throughout the rest of the Arduino workshop series.\n\nThe cl
 ass will consist of a quick introduction to the Arduino platform\, a quick 
 intro and demonstration on how to solder\, and the rest of the class time w
 ill be used for everyone to assemble their ProtoShields.\n\nThe proceeds fr
 om each ticket purchased go directly back into the Node. In this case each 
 ticket will be supplying the Node with a new soldering iron for the worksho
 p and future workshops.\n\nParking is available in the lot North of the bui
 lding on Howard.\n\n*If anyone would like to avoid online fees by paying in
  cash or by check\, please bring the money by the space and leave it in the
  dues tin with a note with your name\, email address\, and that the money i
 s for the arduino workshop. Please do this before the ticket close date so 
 I can get the order in.*\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20230110T144705Z
LOCATION:120 W. North Ave Baltimore\, MD 21201
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Workshops: Learn to Solder
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
